###API:
"""
// kdsCondition:  a javascript condition expression, cannot be a function, and cannot be a javascript template, just be a string.

// KDS.collect(content:'orders'|'items'|'', condition, target, periodical) - the function used by 'collect', 'collect by'。The collect function defines the rules of display items inside each rectangle card, a rectangle card is called a 'collection'.  For example, if you require each collection contains the items with the same name, then you should call the collect("items'', "" ,"#.n"). 

   content: can be 'orders', 'items' or '', defines what you are trying to collect . 
    - 'orders': the listed items inside the collection are orders. 
    - 'items': the listed items inside the collection are items. 
    - '': the listed items inside the collection are items belong to a single order。
   condition : it is a kdsCondition。 
   target: it is one of the NAME_SPACE to add the items with the same NAME_SPACE into a collection。Additionally, You can use "all" to put all the items into a single collection, it is used to show all the items without split items into separate collections. 
   periodical: it is true if polling periotically, otherwise false. default is false。 

// KDS.filter(content:'items'|'', collectionFilter, itemFilter, allFilter:true | false) - the function used by filter, filter by。it has 4 parameters。 
 content: can be 'items' or '', defines the targets we want to display after filter. 
   - 'items': we want to filter items basing the conditions, it will hide the items inside collection if the conditions not match. 
   - '': we want to filter collections。
 collectionFilter : the filter condition for collection. it is describe as collection level filter or collection filter condition. it is a kdsCondition。 
 itemFilter   : the filter condition for item level. it is describe as items filter, item level filter, or items filter condition. it is a kdsCondition. 
 allFilter: if all items need to fullfill or all items must meet, it is true. otherwise it is false.

// KDS.sort(sortType: 'items'|'', sortTarget, ascend, groupTarget, groupAscend|'merge', mergeTarget|'') - the function used by sort, sort by. 
  sortType : if it is 'items', sort the items inside the collection. If sortType is '', sort the collections. 
  sortTarget : the sorting target. it is one of the NAME_SPACE。
  ascend: the sorting target ascend flag. true means ascend, false means descend。 
  groupTarget: the grouping target. it is one of the NAME_SPACE。 
  groupAscend: the grouping ascend flag. true means ascend, false means descend. 'merge' means to merge the group into one item.
  mergeTarget : It is the target to merge two collections. it is one of the NAME_SPACE, default is ''。

// KDS.alert(alertType: 'items'|'', condition, play_sound:true|false) - the function used by alert, alert by. 
  alertType: can be 'orders', 'items' or ''. 
  condition: the alert condition, it is a kdsCondition. 
  play_sound: true means play a sound, otherwise false.

// KDS.layout(layoutType: 'items'|'', styles) - the function used by layout, layout by. 
  layoutType: specifies either "items" or an empty string "". 
  styles: it is an javascript object. in the object, ###itemPerPage### defines how many collection to display in a page; ###height### defines the height of each collection, default does not have height property; ###itemTemplate### defined which template to show the data, the vailable templates are "summary", default does not have template property. ###mode### can be "" or "combo", if "combo" mode, default does not have mode property. when user click the details, system will show full size at right side.

